tree.n.01.defn: a tall perennial woody plant having a main trunk and branches forming a distinct elevated crown; includes both gymnosperms and angiosperms

tree.n.02.defn: a figure that branches from a single root

tree.n.03.defn: English actor and theatrical producer noted for his lavish productions of Shakespeare (1853-1917)

genus.n.02.defn: (biology) taxonomic group containing one or more species
